body.body: Service Bulletin 559 - E5 E10 Fuel Directive and Radio Equipment Devices (RED) Directive 2014/53
Subject: E5 and E10 Fuel Label and Addendum
Tiger XRX, Tiger XRX LRH, Tiger XR, Tiger XRT, Tiger XCX, Tiger XCX LRH, Tiger XC, Tiger XCA
Tiger 800 XR, Tiger 800 XC, Tiger 800 XRT, Tiger 800 XCA, Tiger 800 XCX LRH, Tiger 800 XRX LRH
Tiger Explorer XCA, Tiger Explorer XCX, Tiger Explorer XCX LRH, Tiger Explorer XR, Tiger Explorer XRT, Tiger Explorer XRX, Tiger Explorer XRX LRH
Tiger 1200 XR, Tiger 1200 XRX, Tiger 1200 XCX, Tiger 1200 XRT, Tiger 1200 XCA, Tiger 1200 XRX LRH

Street Twin, Street Scrambler, Street Cup, Bonneville T100, Bonneville T100 Black, Bonneville T120, Bonneville T120 Black, Thruxton, Thruxton R, Bonneville Bobber, Bonneville Bobber Black, Speedmaster
Thunderbird Storm ABS A1, Thunderbird LT ABS A1
Street Triple S, Street Triple R and Street Triple RS
New motorcycles sold within the European Union from October 12
2018 require a fuel quality label to be fitted to the fuel tank on all motorcycles. This information must also be included in the Owner's Handbook.
New motorcycles sold and delivered to customers within the European Union before October 11

To make sure these motorcycles are compliant with the new regulations the relevant fuel quality label must be fitted to the fuel tank and an addendum page inserted into the Owner's Handbook prior to customer delivery.
The addendum page consists of the E5 and E10 Fuel Directive and a Radio Equipment Device Directive 2014/53. A printable addendum page is attached to this service bulletin.
Dealers are required to check their motorcycle stock and if required:
Fit a self adhesive fuel label to the fuel tank.
Print the addendum page and insert it into the owner's handbook.
There are two label options described in the Genuine Parts Information section of this bulletin.
The correct label must be fitted to the relevant motorcycle.
Service Bulletin - Customer Contact Instructions Prior to Delivery
Motorcycles in Dealer Stock on October 12
Service Bulletin - Note - Identification of Affected Motorcycles - Fuel label/addendum
Some affected motorcycles listed in the VIN range will have had the label or the addendum installed by Triumph prior to their release from the factory.
Unmodified motorcycles can be identified by checking the ‘VIN Enquiry’ on www.triumphonline.net.
Fit the relevant self adhesive fuel label to motorcycle and the addendum page to Owner's Handbook
0.05 hours (this includes an allowance for printing the addendum)
Fit the addendum page only to Owner's Handbook
0.03 hours (this includes an allowance for printing the addendum)
Fit the relevant self adhesive fuel label only to the motorcycle
Thunderbird Storm ABS A1, Thunderbird LT ABS A1 from VIN 780498
Tiger Explorer XCA, Tiger Explorer XCX, Tiger Explorer XCX LRH, Tiger Explorer XR, Tiger Explorer XRT, Tiger Explorer XRX, Tiger Explorer XRX LRH up to VIN 846949
Tiger 1200 XR, Tiger 1200 XRX, Tiger 1200 XCX, Tiger 1200 XRT, Tiger 1200 XCA, Tiger 1200 XRX LRH from VIN 852216
Street Twin, Street Scrambler, Street Cup, Bonneville T100, Bonneville T100 Black, Bonneville T120, Bonneville T120 Black, Thruxton, Thruxton R, Bonneville Bobber from VIN 731919
Tiger 800 XR, Tiger 800 XC, Tiger 800 XRT, Tiger 800 XCA, Tiger 800 XCX LRH, Tiger 800 XRX LRH from VIN 855532
Street Triple S, Street Triple R and Street Triple RS from VIN 800262
Speed Triple 1050 from VIN 735438 up to VIN 846800
Speed Triple 1050R from VIN 735337 up to VIN 858022
For Triumph Subsidiary and Overseas Distributor dealers using Triumph Warranty On-Line with Parts Auto Ordering Flag switched on:

Order all repair parts by submitting a New Prior through the Warranty On-Line system. Entering the above repair code in a New Prior will automatically add the parts required and labour times for this Service Bulletin.
Service Bulletin - Genuine Parts Return Instructions - Not Applicable
Service Bulletin - Other Instructions - Not applicable
Fitting the Addendum Page to the Owners Handbook
Print a copy of the addendum page that is attached to this document.
Fold the addendum page as required to fit into the Owner's Handbook.
Insert the addendum page between the last page and the rear cover of the Owner's Handbook.
Fit the E5 E10 fuel label in a position close to the fuel filler cap, in the area adjacent to the warning labels and visible to the rider.
Using a soft lint free cloth, clean the area of the fuel tank where the fuel label is to be fitted.
Carefully peel off the backing sheet and fit the fuel label to the fuel tank.
Circulation Box - use inside bulletin structure
Initial and date when read and return to central file holder
